        But not everyone was pleased with the remake of The Jungle Book, and it looks like there are some people worried about Disney's latest attempt at re-creating a classic for a new audience. 
    
        
            Skip Twitter post  by @_sowrongitsalex
            
                I have such mixed feelings about The Lion King remake. My favourite film in the entire world and I’m so concerned the new version is absolutely awful.— Alex ✨ (@_sowrongitsalex) November 22, 2018

            Report
            
            End of Twitter post  by @_sowrongitsalex
        
    

As well as The Jungle Book, Disney remade Beauty and the Beast (with Emma Watson), and Aladdin is set to be released next year. 
    
        
            Skip Twitter post  by @TheLuxNoctis
            
                Is it just me or does anyone else think the CGI in these Disney remakes is going to age horribly?Don't get me wrong, the new Lion King looks impressively detailed but we're definitely knee-deep in the uncanny valley. Beast from Beauty & the Beast looked awful from day one.— Lux Noctis (@TheLuxNoctis) November 23, 2018

            Report
            
            End of Twitter post  by @TheLuxNoctis
        
    


                
                
                
                
                
            
            
        Are people going to get bored of seeing their favourite stories told again and again? 
    
        
            Skip Twitter post  by @bevelandembosse
            
                Isn’t it gonna be the same story? Same ending? I don’t get the hype. So now they gonna remake every animation? That’s just lazy— ジエシー (@bevelandembosse) November 23, 2018

            Report
            
            End of Twitter post  by @bevelandembosse
        
    

Last year Newsbeat spoke to the cast of London's Lion King musical about the new film.And Janique Charles, who plays Nala in the West End, had some advice for Beyonce. 
    
      
              
